Accessing string Array without ngFor <br>
{{stringArray1}} <br><br>

Accessing stringArray with ngFor <br>
<div *ngIf='stringArray1.length>0;then ShowData else noData'>

</div>

<ng-template #ShowData>
    <ul>
        <li *ngFor="let post of stringArray1;let i=index">{{post}}
        <button (click)="RemovePost(i)"> Delete </button><br><br>
        </li>

    </ul><br>   
</ng-template>

<ng-template #noData >
    <p style="color: red;"> No Data to Show! </p>
</ng-template>

<br><button (click)="AddPost()">Add Post</button><br><br>


Accessing Entire Object Array with ngFor
<ul>
    <li *ngFor="let object of objects">{{object|json}}</li>
</ul><br><br>

Accessing Entire Object property with ngFor
<ul>
    <li *ngFor="let object of objects">{{object.title}}</li>
</ul><br><br>

<button (click)='setStep()'>Step1</button>
<button (click)='setStep()'>Step2</button>
